OL,4,CCovid: Deaf campaigner takes legal
OL,5,Caction over No 10 briefings
OL,6, A deaf campaigner is taking legal
OL,7, action against the government, after
OL,8, complaining that it failed to provide
OL,9, in-person British Sign Language (BSL)
OL,10, interpreters at No 10 Covid briefings.
OL,12,FKatherine Rowley, 36, from Leeds, says
OL,13,Fthe government breached its obligations
OL,14,Funder the Equality Act to make
OL,15,Fbroadcasts accessible to deaf people.
OL,17,FShe says the failure to convey vital
OL,18,Ffacts led to "stress and frustration".
OL,20,FThe government said it was "committed
OL,21,Fto supporting disabled people".
